1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Women of the Storm on the occasion of its twentieth anniversary.
3 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Women of the Storm for its continued
4 advocacy on behalf of businesses and communities throughout the Gulf Coast and to
5 commend the organization on the occasion of its twentieth anniversary; and
6 WHEREAS, Women of the Storm is a nonpartisan, nonpolitical alliance formed in
7 2005 by women whose families, businesses, and lives were affected by Hurricanes Katrina
8 and Rita; and
9 WHEREAS, the organization is comprised of a diverse group of one hundred thirty
10 individuals; it is led by twelve dedicated women who have met nearly every Monday since
11 January 2006 to set an agenda and discuss projects and programs; and
12 WHEREAS, Women of the Storm has been joined by hundreds of individuals who
13 are passionate about rebuilding their homes, businesses, and communities, and the
14 organization is supported by national partners that include LINKS, the Junior League, the
15 Women's Leadership Initiative of United Way, and the National Council of Jewish Women;
16 and
17 WHEREAS, Women of the Storm's original mission was to draw the attention of
18 Congress, the national media, and policy leaders towards the needs of post-Katrina New
19 Orleans, post-Rita South Louisiana, and the entire Gulf Coast; although these areas are
20 culturally, socially, and economically diverse, the members share a passion for their
21 communities; and
